{
  "stem": "7506.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] We stayed basically in the barrack, and as became known to me and the other children at that time, there was a Polish woman-- one of those women that started doing with us when we were first told go to the barrack, turned out to be a Polish woman who to me, when I was 12, seemed an old lady.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Old.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was, at that time, probably 27, 28 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But to a boy of 12, that's old.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES] That woman started looking after us, started somehow mysteriously bringing food to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I knew her by the name of Luba.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "L-U-B-A.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's all I knew about her, that this woman, Luba, seemed to be in charge of us, seemed to concern herself with us, and bring food.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES] Soup, which, you know, like, watery kind of soup.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Sometimes bread.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we did have, at that time, I remember so distinctly, sometimes white bread.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, white bread in the war is like-- was like gold dust.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "First of all, bread is like gold dust.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But then to get it white is even better than gold dust, because the bread we had gotten in Belsen, [PAUSES] and not on a very regular basis, was the German army bread, the kriegs.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So white bread was something very special.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this woman, of course, forged with me personally, through my personal experience, and with the other children, a very special relationship.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That woman became to us like our mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES] That time, we had-- one time I remember-- and it happened on various occasions-- I would look over, up in the sky, and I would see, high above sky, trails of aircraft.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
